&lt;p&gt;TAUNTON AND SOMERSET NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MUSGROVE PARK HOSPITAL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated and Urgent Care Services Directorate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiology Department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiographer Band 3 - 29 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department is recruiting to its’ team of Cardiographers. The team provides non-invasive diagnostic services which includes;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ECG’s in the Department and on the wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;24 hour ambulatory blood pressure recording&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;24 hour, 3 day and 7 day ambulatory ECG recordings with reports&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Treadmill exercise tests&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tilt tests&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cardiographers carry out their work independently except for treadmill and tilt tests where at present they support a Cardiac Physiologist or Doctor. They report directly to Consultants, Cardiac Physiologists and other medical staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training will be provided in all areas of the job description, previous experience would be an advantage but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information contact EllaineThompson tel 01823 342953.&lt;/p&gt;
